<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml version="2.0">

<!-- Advanced Technical Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I HAVE EXPERIENCE WITH *</pattern>
    <template>
        <set name="tech_stack"><star/></set>
        That's impressive! <star/> is a solid choice. 
        <think><set name="tech_mentioned"><star/></set></think>
        
        <condition name="tech_mentioned">
            <li value="PYTHON">Python is fantastic for so many things! Are you more into web development, data science, or something else?</li>
            <li value="JAVASCRIPT">JavaScript is everywhere these days! Do you work more on the frontend, backend, or full-stack?</li>
            <li value="REACT">React is such a powerful framework! How do you handle state management in complex applications?</li>
            <li value="DJANGO">Django is great for rapid development! What's your favorite feature of the framework?</li>
            <li value="AWS">Cloud experience is so valuable! Which AWS services do you work with most?</li>
            <li value="DOCKER">Containerization is essential nowadays! How do you use Docker in your workflow?</li>
            <li>That's a great technology to have in your toolkit! Tell me more about how you use it in your projects.</li>
        </condition>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Problem-Solving Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I WOULD USE *</pattern>
    <template>
        <set name="solution_approach"><star/></set>
        That's a solid approach! Using <star/> shows good technical judgment.
        
        <random>
            <li>What made you choose that particular solution?</li>
            <li>Have you used that approach in production before?</li>
            <li>What alternatives did you consider?</li>
            <li>How would you handle scaling that solution?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I WOULD * TO SOLVE *</pattern>
    <template>
        Excellent problem-solving approach! <star index="1"/> is a smart way to handle <star index="2"/>.
        
        <random>
            <li>What challenges might you face with that approach?</li>
            <li>How would you test that solution?</li>
            <li>What would be your backup plan if that didn't work?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Architecture and Design Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I WOULD DESIGN * USING *</pattern>
    <template>
        Great architectural thinking! Designing <star index="1"/> with <star index="2"/> shows you understand scalable systems.
        
        <random>
            <li>How would you handle data consistency in that design?</li>
            <li>What about performance bottlenecks - how would you address those?</li>
            <li>How would you monitor and maintain that system?</li>
            <li>What security considerations would you need to think about?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Learning and Growth Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I LEARNED * BY *</pattern>
    <template>
        That's a great way to learn! <star index="2"/> is an effective approach for mastering <star index="1"/>.
        
        <random>
            <li>What was the most challenging part of learning that?</li>
            <li>How do you stay current with new developments in that area?</li>
            <li>What would you recommend to someone just starting with that technology?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I AM CURRENTLY LEARNING *</pattern>
    <template>
        That's awesome! <star/> is definitely worth learning. Continuous learning is so important in tech.
        
        <random>
            <li>What motivated you to start learning that?</li>
            <li>How are you finding the learning process?</li>
            <li>Do you have any projects planned using that technology?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Team and Collaboration Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I WORK WITH A TEAM OF *</pattern>
    <template>
        Team collaboration is crucial! Working with <star/> must give you great diverse perspectives.
        
        <random>
            <li>How do you handle code reviews in your team?</li>
            <li>What's your approach to resolving technical disagreements?</li>
            <li>How do you share knowledge within the team?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I PREFER * OVER *</pattern>
    <template>
        Interesting preference! Choosing <star index="1"/> over <star index="2"/> suggests you've thought about the trade-offs.
        
        <random>
            <li>What specific advantages does that give you?</li>
            <li>Are there situations where you might choose the alternative?</li>
            <li>How did you come to that conclusion?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Challenge and Problem Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>THE BIGGEST CHALLENGE WAS *</pattern>
    <template>
        Challenges like <star/> really test your problem-solving skills! 
        
        <random>
            <li>How did you approach solving that challenge?</li>
            <li>What did you learn from that experience?</li>
            <li>Would you handle it differently now?</li>
            <li>Did you get help from others or solve it independently?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I HAD TO DEBUG *</pattern>
    <template>
        Debugging <star/> can be tricky! That's a valuable skill to have.
        
        <random>
            <li>What's your systematic approach to debugging?</li>
            <li>What tools do you use for debugging?</li>
            <li>How do you prevent similar issues in the future?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

